Troubleshooting
API server not responding:

Check if process is running: ps aux | grep api_server
Verify port 5000 is not in use: netstat -tlnp | grep 5000
Check for Python errors in terminal output
Worker not fetching jobs:

Verify API_BASE_URL is correct in worker_service.py
Test API manually: curl http://localhost:5000/jobs?status=pending
Check for network/connection errors in worker output
Jobs stuck in 'processing' status:

Worker may have crashed during execution
Check for exceptions in worker terminal
Manually reset job status in database if needed:
sqlite3 jobs.db "UPDATE jobs SET status='pending' WHERE status='processing';"
Permission errors during job execution:

Ensure worker has permissions for backup/cleanup directories
Use /tmp for testing instead of system directories
Check file ownership: ls -la /path/to/directory
